I agree that Dispatches was good.<br><br>
One of the best books I've read though was &quot;Dak To&quot; by Edward F. Murphy.<br><br>
It combines straight history with first-person accounts and is believeable.<br><br>
Not like so much of that &quot;I was a Seal Commando&quot; trash that's out there.  Cannon Fodder for examplee.  Truly an account by a phony.<br><br>
But Murphy's book is good as are books by Leonard White (fictional or not).
